x = \frac{3 \pm \sqrt{(-3)^2 - 4(5)(-5)}}{2(5)} = \frac{3 \pm \sqrt{9 + 100}}{10} = \frac{3 \pm \sqrt{109}}{10}
\] Next, we need to find the value of \((10x - 3)^2\). We will substitute the solutions for \(x\) into this expression and simplify. First, consider \(10x - 3\) for \(x = \frac{3 + \sqrt{109}}{10}\): \[
10x - 3 = 10 \left( \frac{3 + \sqrt{109}}{10} \right) - 3 = 3 + \sqrt{109} - 3 = \sqrt{109}
\] So \((10x - 3)^2 = (\sqrt{109})^2 = 109\). Similarly, for \(x = \frac{3 - \sqrt{109}}{10}\): \[
10x - 3 = 10 \left( \frac{3 - \sqrt{109}}{10} \right) - 3 = 3 - \sqrt{109} - 3 = -\sqrt{109}
\] So \((10x - 3)^2 = (-\sqrt{109})^2 = 109\). In both cases, the value of \((10x - 3)^2\) is 109. Thus, the final answer is \(\boxed{109}\). </think> <answer> 109 </answer>
